LunarWing is NOT a corporate startup. LunarWing is not trying to make money off of you or sell you bullshit cloud services. We DO NOT sell access to LLMs. We are NOT NearAI. See README.md and FORK_CONTEXT.md for more information as to why this hard fork has been created as well as a partial list of the brand new features that do not exist in upstream Ironclaw. (at some point a full list of additional features which are not included in the upstream repo will be added)

LunarWing supports autonomous political formations.

LunarWing supports the Free Software Foundation.

LunarWing supports freedom, user choice, locally hosted LLM set ups, various TEE environments, and less secure options of using LLMs. It is entirely up to the user how much trust you have in your model providers. 

While we do support user choice, we do not necessarily want to pander to randoms online to support x, y, or z tool out of the box besides the ones which are core to the LunarWing project. This certainly means that no, we won't officially support proprietary communication channels, even if the code exists in the repo. Users can use it, but it will certainly not be updated or supported in the future. The team may, at its own discretion, even choose to entirely remove any or all of these channel source code components in the repo which disagrees with our philosophy. You have been warned. This includes channels such as: Slack, Signal, Telegram, Discord, Whatsapp, or whatever other normie shit comes with Ironclaw. The LunarWing team uses secure, private, self-hostable communication methods such as Weechat IRC with end to end encryption on the plugin level (See: Enjin), DarkIRC and XMPP MUC chats with OMEMO encryption. We do use various locally developed MCP servers as well for our agents. We utilize our own notification servers and do not use Google services either, so these will also not be supported or given any love.

LunarWing is also not a democratic organization into itself. We are a private collective with very opinionated backgrounds in cybersecurity. Our own opinions and philosophy will have an impact on this project going forward. Our opinions, experience, and philosophy WILL have an impact on what we choose to focus on for LunarWing. We all work as volunteers on this project and do not earn a salary or any compensation whatsoever for our work. We do want anyone to be able to participate and contibute, but please keep in mind that we are not a democracy and you do not get a vote on what will be included or not. Any proposed changes to the codebase will be stringently reviewed by the core developers and decided on before being merged into the project.

Disclaimer: LunarWing has nothing in terms of external security audits yet. Consider all of this alpha or beta software for the time being.
